Return a dict with the following structure:

```
{
    "<read_type (paired end)>": {
        "<folder_name_1>": [
            [
                <ResultFile uuid=f12822f5-8801-49e0-9871-9647beae2cb7>,
                <ResultFile uuid=819ec7a5-47ea-43a1-a861-589326b273c6>
            ]
        ],
    },
    "<read_type (single end)>": {
        "<folder_name_1>": [
                <ResultFile uuid=eaaaf0c4-883f-4e7b-89c0-8b57552596ea>
        ],
}
```

Does not download the files.

A class to connect filepaths on the local system to GeoSeeq Results.

Available Patterns:
 - {parent_obj_name}
 - {result_name}
 - {result_replicate} (replicate number of the result)
 - {field_name}
 - {field_checksum} (checksum of the data stored in field)
 - {field_updated_at} (timestamp when the field was last updated)
 - {ext} (file extension)
